The '''Ghana Chamber of Telecommunications''' is an [[umbrella organization]] that regulates and promotes the interests of Telecommunication companies in [[Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://telecomschamber.com/|title=Home - Ghana Chambers of Telecommunication|website=Ghana Chambers of Telecommunication|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nca.org.gh/media-and-news/news/chamber-of-telecoms-honours-communications-minister-and-nca-dg/|title=Chamber of Telecoms Honours Communications Minister and NCA DG » National Communications Authority|website=nca.org.gh|language=en|access-date=2017-11-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://citifmonline.com/2017/04/09/kwaku-sakyi-addo-steps-down-as-telecoms-chamber-ceo/|title=Kwaku Sakyi-Addo steps down as Telecoms Chamber CEO {{!}}|website=citifmonline.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-17}}</ref> The Chamber is headed by Kweku Sakyi-Addo<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://theheraldghana.com/telecom-chamber-sack-kweku-sakyi-addo/|title=Telecom Chamber To Sack Kweku Sakyi-Addo|work=Herald|access-date=2017-11-17|language=en-US}}</ref>

